  <data name="toolTipTitleItem4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>&lt;b&gt;Direct&lt;/b&gt;: In Direct mode, the software checks each rule one at a time, in the order you've set. This order can affect the results, so it’s important to carefully arrange the rules at the start to get the best match. This mode allows for more control over how matches are found but requires some attention to rule ordering.
 
&lt;b&gt;Mixed:&lt;/b&gt; In Mixed mode, all the rules are checked at once, so the order you set is less important. This mode is useful if you don’t need precise control over rule sequence, though it may take a bit longer to process due to the simultaneous checks.</value>
  </data>
